[[Image:Sana'a Museum.jpg|thumb|''Dar al-Shukr'' palace in Sana'a (1986)]]
[[File:Museum of Traditional Arts & Crafts in Sana'a.JPG|thumb|Main gate to the palace (2007)]]
'''Dar al-Shukr''' (House of Gratefulness) is a royal palace located in [[Sana'a]], Yemen. It is located near Qubbat al-Mutawakkil Mosque dome in [[Tahrir Square, Sana'a|Tahrir Square]] in the city centre.

After the fall of the monarchy in the 1960s, it housed the [[National Museum of Yemen]]. After that it houses the Museum of Traditional Arts and Crafts.

