'''French of France''', sometimes called '''hexagonal French''', is the predominant [[variety (linguistics)|variety]] of the [[French language]] in [[France]], [[Andorra]] and [[Monaco]], in its [[Register (sociolinguistics)#Register as formality scale|formal and informal]] registers. It has, for a long time, been associated with [[Standard French]]. It is now seen as a variety of French alongside [[Quebec French]], [[Swiss French]], [[Belgian French]], etc.

