'''Mahesar''' ({{lang-ur|''' مہیسر '''}}) is a [[Sindhi people|Sindhi]] tribe of [[Samma (tribe)|Samma]] origin in [[Sindh]], Pakistan & some parts of  [[India]]. [[Shah Abdul Latif Bhittai]] in his poetry has used the word of Mahesar which means [[Murshid]] or [[Kamil]] and guiding soul.

Mahesar is a [[Sindhi people|Sindhi]] community cast. Mostly Mahesar community living in Sindh Province, they are also living in other parts of the [[World]] like [[Dubai]] [[Sharjah]] [[KSA]] and other [[Countries]]. 
It means clear that Mahesar means [[Murshid]] or [[Kamil]].

